# Ralplan Workflow

Iterative planning with consensus — Planner proposes, Architect evaluates, Critic challenges, repeat until consensus.

## Trigger Keywords

"ralplan", "consensus plan", "plan with review"

## Process

```
Round 1:
  [Planner]   → Create initial plan → .omc-cursor/plans/{task}.md
  [Architect] → Evaluate feasibility, design concerns
  [Critic]    → Challenge assumptions, find gaps

  If concerns exist → Planner revises plan

Round 2:
  [Planner]   → Revised plan incorporating feedback
  [Architect] → Re-evaluate
  [Critic]    → Re-challenge

  Repeat until: All roles agree (max 3 rounds)

Final:
  Present consensus plan to user → Await approval
```

## Consensus Criteria

A plan reaches consensus when:
- Architect confirms feasibility and sound design
- Critic has no HIGH-severity concerns remaining
- All acceptance criteria are testable
- Risk mitigations are defined for identified risks

## Output

Each round updates `.omc-cursor/plans/{task}.md` with:

```markdown
# Plan: {task}

## Round {N} — {status: DRAFT / REVISED / CONSENSUS}

### Plan
{steps}

### Architect Feedback
{feasibility assessment}

### Critic Feedback
{concerns with severity}

### Changes from Previous Round
{what was revised and why}
```

## Rules

- Maximum 3 rounds — if no consensus, present best version with noted disagreements
- Each role must provide concrete, actionable feedback
- Planner must address every HIGH concern in revision
- Don't over-plan — stop when the plan is "good enough to start"
- Announce role transitions: "Round 2: Switching to Architect role for feasibility review."
